-- South Korea Stocks: Korea Zinc, LG Chem, Poongsan, Ssangyong
-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 2012-03-05T07:53:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-05/south-korea-stocks-korea-zinc-lg-chem-poongsan-ssangyong.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  South Korea trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in  Seoul .  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  dropped 0.9 percent to 2,016.06.  Metal producers: Korea Zinc Co. (010130 KS), which produces
gold and silver, lost 2.3 percent to 418,000 won. Poongsan Corp.
(103140 KS), a copper-products maker, sank 3 percent to 32,300
won. Gold for April delivery fell 0.7 percent in  New York  on
March 2, while silver futures for May delivery fell 3.2 percent.
Copper futures also retreated.  Ssangyong Engineering & Construction Co. (012650)  (012650 KS) added
1.4 percent to 6,580 won, its biggest gain since Feb. 8. State-
run Korea Asset Management Corp. will resume a plan to sell its
stake in Ssangyong Engineering in April, MoneyToday reported,
without saying where it got the information. Officials at Korea
Asset’s public relations team said a detailed plan on how and
when to sell its stake hasn’t been decided.  LG Chem Ltd. (051910)  (051910 KS), the biggest South Korean
chemicals maker, slipped 4.8 percent to 384,500 won, the most
since Dec. 19.  General Motors Co. (GM) , missing sales goals for the
Chevrolet Volt plug-in hybrid, plans to halt production of the
sedan for five weeks starting later this month rather than
discount the high-technology cars. LG Chem supplies Volt
batteries.  To contact the reporter on this story:
